    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks for that. so i've seen some people online saying originalism is basically just a way for judges to hide their own political biases behind \"history\" instead of actually following the law. how would a scholar respond to the critique that originalism is just a tool for partisan outcomes?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
